reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really striking design, easy assembly, but not a ton of surface space
reviews.reviewText: If you're anything like me, you got a whole new bedroom. The one you shared with the love of your life left you sleepless, wondering how it all went so hopelessly wrong. Well, friends, if you're looking to upgrade, you can't do much better than these puppies. Assembly was quite easy, with extra pieces provided in case you were to lose any - both nightstands were together within the better part of an hour. The lighting is nice and pretty subtle even while sleeping, but I would advise against using any blue shades at night.The only thing I don't love about these is the surface space. The power strip is banging, no doubt about that, but does take up a small portion of the top. The second shelf and the two drawers mitigate this space issue, but depending on how tall your bed is, you may find the lower shelves unreachable. Anyhow, I love em and they beat the heck out of the heavy, wooden ones I used to have.
